    "body": "# Followup\r\n\r\nI manually typed the variable instead of importing its type and I encountered another error:\r\n\r\n```\r\n/Users/chriskrogh/dev/dot/token/test/DotToken.test.ts:4\r\n  let instance: { address: string };\r\n              ^\r\n\r\nSyntaxError: Unexpected token ':'\r\n    at compileFunction (<anonymous>)\r\n    ...\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt seems like the issue here is the way that the TypeScript is being transpiled for the tests to run. I think the fix may be an update to the tsconfig being used for tests.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, you could let developers modify this config themselves? Maybe developers can add their config to a `tsconfig.testing.json` and then specify the path to this config file somewhere in the `truffle-config.js`?",
